{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#github-app-permissions", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "github-app-permissions", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Admin setup > GitHub App permissions", "level": 3, "position": 3, "text": "The manifest configures the GitHub App with the permissions and webhook events Claude needs across web sessions, Code Review, and contribution metrics:\n\nThe app subscribes to `pull_request`, `issue_comment`, `pull_request_review_comment`, `pull_request_review`, and `check_run` events.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#admin-setup", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#manual-setup", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "manual-setup", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Admin setup > Manual setup", "level": 3, "position": 4, "text": "If the guided redirect flow is blocked by your network configuration, click Add manually instead of Connect. Create a GitHub App on your GHES instance with the permissions and events above, then enter the app credentials in the form: hostname, OAuth client ID and secret, GitHub App ID, client ID, client secret, webhook secret, and private key.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#admin-setup", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#network-requirements", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "network-requirements", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Admin setup > Network requirements", "level": 3, "position": 5, "text": "Your GHES instance must be reachable from Anthropic infrastructure so Claude can clone repositories and post review comments. If your GHES instance is behind a firewall, allowlist the Anthropic API IP addresses.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#admin-setup", "external_links": ["https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/api/ip-addresses"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#admin-setup", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "admin-setup", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Admin setup", "level": 2, "position": 2, "text": "An admin connects your GHES instance to Claude Code once. After that, developers in your organization can use GHES repositories without any additional configuration. You need admin access to your Claude organization and permission to create GitHub Apps on your GHES instance.\n\nThe guided setup generates a GitHub App manifest and redirects you to your GHES instance to create the app in one click. If your environment blocks the redirect flow, an alternative manual setup is available.\n\nOpen Claude Code admin settings\n\nGo to claude.ai/admin-settings/claude-code and find the GitHub Enterprise Server section.\n\nStart the guided setup\n\nClick Connect. Enter a display name for the connection and your GHES hostname, for example `github.example.com`. If your GHES instance uses a self-signed or private certificate authority, paste the CA certificate in the optional field.\n\nCreate the GitHub App\n\nClick Continue to GitHub Enterprise. Your browser redirects to your GHES instance with a pre-filled app manifest. Review the configuration and click Create GitHub App. GHES redirects you back to Claude with the app credentials stored automatically.\n\nInstall the app on your repositories\n\nFrom the GitHub App page on your GHES instance, install the app on the repositories or organizations you want Claude to access. You can start with a subset and add more later.\n\nEnable features\n\nReturn to claude.ai/admin-settings/claude-code and enable Code Review and contribution metrics for your GHES repositories using the same configuration as github.com.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["http://github.com", "https://claude.ai/admin-settings/claude-code"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "737dacb464461d64", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#developer-workflow", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "git clone git@github.example.com:platform/api-service.git\ncd api-service", "preceding_paragraph": "Clone a repository from your GHES instance as you normally would:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "8474cd8fe5385b50", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#developer-workflow", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "claude --remote \"Add retry logic to the payment webhook handler\"", "preceding_paragraph": "Then start a web session. Claude detects the GHES host from your git remote and routes the session through your organization's configured instance:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#teleport-sessions-to-your-terminal", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "teleport-sessions-to-your-terminal", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Developer workflow > Teleport sessions to your terminal", "level": 3, "position": 7, "text": "Pull a web session into your local terminal with `claude --teleport`. Teleport verifies you're in a checkout of the same GHES repository before fetching the branch and loading the session history. See teleport requirements for details.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#developer-workflow", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#developer-workflow", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "developer-workflow", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Developer workflow", "level": 2, "position": 6, "text": "Once your admin has connected the GHES instance, no developer-side configuration is needed. Claude Code detects your GHES hostname automatically from the git remote in your working directory.\n\nClone a repository from your GHES instance as you normally would:\n\nThen start a web session. Claude detects the GHES host from your git remote and routes the session through your organization's configured instance:\n\nThe session runs on Anthropic infrastructure, clones your repository from GHES, and pushes changes back to a branch. Monitor progress with `/tasks` or at claude.ai/code. See Claude Code on the web for the full remote session workflow including diff review, auto-fix, and routines.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["https://claude.ai/code"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "3f9ac50d77de31d2", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#add-a-ghes-marketplace", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "/plugin marketplace add git@github.example.com:platform/claude-plugins.git", "preceding_paragraph": "The `owner/repo` shorthand always resolves to github.com. For GHES-hosted marketplaces, use the full git URL:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "889031f4e7263bde", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#add-a-ghes-marketplace", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "/plugin marketplace add https://github.example.com/platform/claude-plugins.git", "preceding_paragraph": "HTTPS URLs work as well:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#add-a-ghes-marketplace", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "add-a-ghes-marketplace", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Plugin marketplaces on GHES > Add a GHES marketplace", "level": 3, "position": 9, "text": "The `owner/repo` shorthand always resolves to github.com. For GHES-hosted marketplaces, use the full git URL:\n\nHTTPS URLs work as well:\n\nSee Create and distribute a plugin marketplace for the full guide to building marketplaces.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#plugin-marketplaces-on-ghes", "external_links": ["http://github.com"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "8428a42509b69913", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#allowlist-ghes-marketplaces-in-managed-settings", "position": 0, "language": "json", "text": "{\n  \"strictKnownMarketplaces\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"hostPattern\",\n      \"hostPattern\": \"^github\\\\.example\\\\.com$\"\n    }\n  ]\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "If your organization uses managed settings to restrict which marketplaces developers can add, use the `hostPattern` source type to allow all marketplaces from your GHES instance without enumerating each repository:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7ed31f57dd334a4a", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#allowlist-ghes-marketplaces-in-managed-settings", "position": 1, "language": "json", "text": "{\n  \"extraKnownMarketplaces\": {\n    \"internal-tools\": {\n      \"source\": {\n        \"source\": \"git\",\n        \"url\": \"git@github.example.com:platform/claude-plugins.git\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "You can also pre-register marketplaces for developers so they appear without manual setup. This example makes an internal tools marketplace available organization-wide:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#allowlist-ghes-marketplaces-in-managed-settings", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "allowlist-ghes-marketplaces-in-managed-settings", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Plugin marketplaces on GHES > Allowlist GHES marketplaces in managed settings", "level": 3, "position": 10, "text": "If your organization uses managed settings to restrict which marketplaces developers can add, use the `hostPattern` source type to allow all marketplaces from your GHES instance without enumerating each repository:\n\nYou can also pre-register marketplaces for developers so they appear without manual setup. This example makes an internal tools marketplace available organization-wide:\n\nSee the strictKnownMarketplaces and extraKnownMarketplaces settings reference for the complete schema.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#plugin-marketplaces-on-ghes", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#plugin-marketplaces-on-ghes", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "plugin-marketplaces-on-ghes", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Plugin marketplaces on GHES", "level": 2, "position": 8, "text": "Host plugin marketplaces on your GHES instance to distribute internal tooling across your organization. The marketplace structure is identical to github.com-hosted marketplaces; the only difference is how you reference them.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#limitations", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "limitations", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Limitations", "level": 2, "position": 11, "text": "A few features behave differently on GHES than on github.com. The feature table summarizes support; this section covers the workarounds.\n\n- `/install-github-app` command: follow the admin setup flow on claude.ai instead. If you also want GitHub Actions workflows on GHES, adapt the example workflow manually.\n- GitHub MCP server: use the `gh` CLI configured for your GHES host instead. Run `gh auth login --hostname github.example.com` to authenticate, then Claude can use `gh` commands in sessions.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["http://claude.ai", "http://github.com", "https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code-action/blob/main/examples/claude.yml"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#web-session-fails-to-clone-repository", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "web-session-fails-to-clone-repository", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Troubleshooting > Web session fails to clone repository", "level": 3, "position": 13, "text": "If `claude --remote` fails with a clone error, verify that your admin has completed setup for your GHES instance and that the GitHub App is installed on the repository you're working in. Check with your admin that the instance hostname registered in Claude settings matches the hostname in your git remote.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#troubleshooting", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#marketplace-add-fails-with-a-policy-error", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "marketplace-add-fails-with-a-policy-error", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Troubleshooting > Marketplace add fails with a policy error", "level": 3, "position": 14, "text": "If `/plugin marketplace add` is blocked for your GHES URL, your organization has restricted marketplace sources. Ask your admin to add a `hostPattern` entry for your GHES hostname in managed settings.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#troubleshooting", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#ghes-instance-not-reachable", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "ghes-instance-not-reachable", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Troubleshooting > GHES instance not reachable", "level": 3, "position": 15, "text": "If reviews or web sessions time out, your GHES instance may not be reachable from Anthropic infrastructure. Confirm your firewall allows inbound connections from the Anthropic API IP addresses.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#troubleshooting", "external_links": ["https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/api/ip-addresses"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#troubleshooting", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "troubleshooting", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Troubleshooting", "level": 2, "position": 12, "text": "", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md#related-resources", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/github-enterprise-server.md", "anchor": "related-resources", "breadcrumb": "Claude Code with GitHub Enterprise Server > Related resources", "level": 2, "position": 16, "text": "These pages cover the features referenced throughout this guide in more depth:\n\n- Claude Code on the web: run Claude Code sessions on cloud infrastructure\n- Code Review: automated PR reviews\n- Plugin marketplaces: build and distribute plugin catalogs\n- Analytics: track usage and contribution metrics\n- Managed settings: organization-wide policy configuration\n- Network configuration: firewall and IP allowlist requirements", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
